This paper investigates the power-performance tradeoffs in data center servers, which is a topic related to distributed computing and systems (cs.DC). The use of DVFS and CPU pinning also falls under the category of computer architecture (cs.AR). The paper also discusses load balancing strategies, which is a topic related to control systems (cs.SY) and performance analysis (cs.PF). Finally, the experiments performed in the paper involve running replicas of the German Wikipedia, which is a topic related to software engineering (cs.SE).
